MIAMI MAKES SIX ERRORS BUT ADVANCES IN SERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Danny Buxbaum's two-run double in the seventh inning helped Miami overcome six 
errors as the top-seeded Hurricanes stayed alive Monday in the College World 
Series with a 7-5 victory over Auburn. 
</P>
<P>
 "That's probably about as ugly a win as we've ever had," said a relieved 
