<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: YOU DESERVE SOME GRITS TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Bloomberg Business News 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When in the South, do as Southerners do: Eat grits for breakfast.In a handful 
of Mississippi outlets, McDonald's Corp. is test-marketing grits. 
</P>
<P>
 "They taste pretty good," said Volanda Williams, spooning down a cup of grits 
along with an Egg McMuffin at the McDonald's in Forest, Miss. "They taste 
better at home, of course." 
</P>
<P>
 For the non-cognoscenti, grits are oats that have been husked but not ground. 
"McGrits" cost 49 cents a cup. 
</P>
