<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASEBALL WORLD SERIES; ARIZONA ST. EDGED BY OKLAHOMA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rick Gutierrez's sacrifice fly in the 11th inning gave Oklahoma a 4-3 victory 
over Arizona State on Monday night in the winners' bracket of the College World 
Series. 
</P>
<P>
 The run broke a string of seven scoreless innings by relievers of both teams, 
with each team's ace getting the decision -- Bucky Buckles (4-3) for the 
Sooners and Noah Peery (11-2) for Arizona State. 
</P>
<P>
 Peery walked pinch-hitter Dustin Hansen to lead off the 11th and a sacrifice 
bunt and passed ball got him to third for Gutierrez's fly ball to center. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sun Devils (44-17) will play Miami, a 7-5 winner over Auburn on Monday, in 
an elimination game today. Oklahoma (48-17) will await the winner of that game 
in a Thursday afternoon semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
 Danny Buxbaum's two-run double in the seventh helped top-seeded Miami overcome 
six errors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
