<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJORS; CLUB OWNERS WILL BEGIN MEETINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Club owners will begin three days of meetings in Cincinnati tonight, with the 
election of a new American League president and discussions of a salary-cap 
proposal topping the agenda. 
</P>
<P>
 Gene Budig, chancellor of the University of Kansas, is the choice to replace 
Bobby Brown as AL president. 
</P>
<P>
 The labor situation is expected to dominate the session. Richard Ravitch, 
management's negotiator, is seeking permission to present a salary-cap proposal 
to the players' association, which is considering whether to strike during the 
second half of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Chicago Cubs placed pitcher Mike Morgan (0-7, 7.75 ERA) on the 15-day 
disabled list so he can attend to personal matters. . . . Florida Marlin 
pitcher Luis Aquino was placed on the 15-day disabled list because of a broken 
little toe on his right foot. . . . Reliever Tim Scott was placed on the 15-day 
disabled list by the Montreal Expos because of tendinitis in his right elbow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
