<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: BANKING & FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rates Fall on Short-Term Treasury Bills: The Treasury Department sold $12.7 
billion in new three-month bills at an average discount rate of 4.15%, down 
from 4.23% last week.Another $12.6 billion of new six-month bills was sold at 
an average discount rate of 4.53%, down from 4.67%. The new discount rates 
understate the actual return to investors: 4.25% for three-month bills, with a 
$10,000 bill selling for $9,895.10, and 4.7% for a six-month bill selling for 
$9,777.10. The discount rate reflects the price discount received when 
government securities are sold at less than face value. T-Bill Auction 
</P>
<P>
 3-month: 4.15% 
</P>
<P>
 6-month: 4.53% 
</P>
</TEXT>
