<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; GAS STATION CLERK INJURED IN ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two men armed with a handgun charged into a Simi Valley gas station early 
Monday, struck the clerk on the head and ran away with a small amount of money, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The men entered Thrifty Gas Station at 2211 Tapo St. at about 2 a.m. and 
forced the clerk to lie on the floor. After hitting the clerk more than once on 
the head, the suspects fled with less than $100, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The clerk was treated for a minor head injury at Simi Valley Hospital and 
released, police said. CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
