<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS : VENTURA; PROJECT WOULD ADD FACILITIES TO CITY PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 By next February, Ventura's Arroyo Verde Park may sport new barbecue grills, 
picnic benches and a children's play area if the City Council approves a plan 
to improve the park's north end. 
</P>
<P>
 The council on Monday approved a report showing that the proposed improvements 
will not have a significant negative impact on the environment. 
</P>
<P>
 City engineers say the project -- which will cost Ventura up to $300,000 -- 
will go out to bid sometime this summer. After bids are submitted, the council 
will take a final vote on the project. 
</P>
<P>
 The improvements will also include a horseshoe pit and a paved parking lot for 
up to 68 cars. 
</P>
<P>
 Arroyo Verde Park covers 130 acres and lies at the end of Day Road on 
Ventura's north side. The park already has barbecue and picnic facilities and 
children's areas on its south end. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
