WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS : VENTURA; DONATED CAR FOR SALE BY NONPROFIT CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A nonprofit Ventura group that specializes in settling neighborhood disputes 
is offering for sale a rebuilt car that the former owner donated after the 
vehicle quit at the top of the Conejo Grade. 
</P>
<P>
 Nina Meierding), a Ventura attorney, gave her 1984 Toyota Celica GTS to the 
Ventura Center for Dispute Settlement. The center works with residents in an 
attempt to settle arguments out of court. Proceeds from the sale of the car 
will go to the center. 
</P>
<P>
 Various local businesses and mechanics donated their services to upgrade the 
car, including installing a rebuilt engine and a new car stereo. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone who is interested in buying the car can contact the center at 650-9202. 
