ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; FITNESS WALKING FOR SENIOR CITIZENS SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Keep walking, and keep healthy. 
</P>
<P>
 That's the theme of an early-morning walking program for senior citizens 
scheduled this summer on the track at Golden West College. 
</P>
<P>
 The 10-session program starts June 24 and continues through Aug. 26. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration is currently underway at the college's Community Services Office. 
The program fee is $26. 
</P>
<P>
 "The program is recommended for all seniors who are new to exercise as well as 
participants in the Golden West College beginning and advanced aerobic-exercise 
workshops," said Lori Thomas, a spokeswoman for the college. 
</P>
<P>
 "Emphasis is placed on breathing and walking posture, and (the class) provides 
a cardiovascular workout, including warm-up, walk-out, cool-down and final 
stretch-out exercises. 
</P>
<P>
 Walking shoes and sweat suits are recommended." 
</P>
<P>
 The instructor for the walking workshop is Ruth E. Bennett, who holds a 
master's degree in education with emphasis on fitness for older adults. 
</P>
<P>
 The walking class is designed for "active seniors, ages 55 to 79," college 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the college's Community Services Office at (714) 
891-3991. BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</TEXT>
