<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SAN FERNANDO; FREE WORKSHOP ON SBA DISASTER LOANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A free workshop to help earthquake-impacted business owners complete forms for 
Small Business Administration disaster loans -- even if they have already been 
turned down -- is scheduled tonight at Mission College's Business and 
Professional Center in San Fernando. 
</P>
<P>
 Taught by representatives of the Small Business Development Center of North 
Los Angeles County, the workshop will begin at 6:30 p.m. in Room 5 of the 
center, at 1300 San Fernando Road. 
</P>
<P>
 "We found that a lot of people, because they hadn't filled out the paperwork 
properly, were being turned down by the SBA," said Ralph Kacy, the center's 
research director. "They didn't realize they could send it back, with 
additional information, to reapply for the loans." 
</P>
<P>
 The California Community Colleges is sponsoring the workshops with a $10,000 
grant, which also pays for individual counseling for business owners. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop will be repeated at 6:30 p.m. on Tuesday, June 21. For more 
information, contact the Business and Professional Center at (818) 837-2236. 
JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</TEXT>
