LOCAL NOTES: MATER DEI CATCHER TREANOR SIGNS WITH ROYALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS FOSTER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Matt Treanor, a catcher from Mater Dei High School, opened a bank account 
Monday, two days after he signed with the Kansas City Royals. 
</P>
<P>
 "I didn't have much money before, but I expect it will be coming in now," 
Treanor said. 
</P>
<P>
 Treanor was a fourth-round selection Thursday in baseball's amateur draft. He 
becomes the first Mater Dei player to sign directly out of high school since 
Bob Ickes became coach 20 years ago. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was a little worried that the scouts might shy away from me because of 
that," Treanor said. "I thought they might not draft me very high." 
</P>
<P>
 Treanor, who said he signed for a little less than $100,000, hit .368 with 
three home runs and 23 runs batted in. He has been assigned to the Royals' 
rookie league team in Ft. Myers, Fla. CHRIS FOSTER 
