<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; DISTRICT GRADUATION DATES APPROACHING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 More than 2,350 high school seniors and adult education students will 
participate in Garden Grove Unified School District's graduation ceremonies on 
June 16, 20 and 21. 
</P>
<P>
 Commencement ceremonies for intermediate schools will be on June 21, said 
district spokesman Alan Trudell. 
</P>
<P>
 Graduation ceremonies will be held on June 20 for: La Quinta High School 
students at 3 p.m. at Bolsa Grande High School stadium; Los Amigos High School 
students at 6 p.m. at Garden Grove High School stadium; Pacifica High School 
students at 6 p.m. at Bolsa Grande High School stadium; Rancho Alamitos High 
School students at 5 p.m. on campus; Santiago High School students at 3 p.m. at 
Garden Grove High School stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Graduation ceremonies will be held on June 20 for: Bolsa Grande High School 
students at 5 p.m. at the school stadium; Garden Grove High School students at 
4:30 p.m. at the campus stadium; and Lake High School students at 7 p.m. on 
campus. 
</P>
<P>
 Adult education ceremonies will be held at 7 p.m. on June 16 at the 
Chapman-Hettinga Education Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Commencement ceremonies will be held for: Alamitos Intermediate School 
students at 2 p.m. at Rancho Alamitos High School; Hilton D. Bell Intermediate 
School students at 2 p.m. at Pacifica High School; Dr. Leroy L. Doig 
Intermediate School students at 1:45 p.m. at Santiago High School; Stephen R. 
Fitz Intermediate School students at 1:30 p.m. at Los Amigos High School; and 
James Irvine Intermediate School students at 1:30 at the Don Wash Auditorium of 
Garden Grove High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Commencement ceremonies will also be held for: Donald S. Jordan Intermediate 
School students at 1:30 p.m. at Bolsa Grande High School; McGarvin Intermediate 
School students at 11 a.m. on campus; Dr. Walter C. Ralston Intermediate School 
students at 11:15 a.m. at the Don Wash Auditorium of Garden Grove High School; 
and Walton Intermediate School students at 9 a.m. at the Don Wash Auditorium of 
Garden Grove High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Trudell said a ceremony will also be held at 11 a.m. on June 21 for students 
attending the Jordan Secondary Learning Center. Fifteen students with 
disabilities will be recognized at that ceremony, which will be held at that 
campus. 
</P>
<P>
 The Garden Grove School District serves most of Garden Grove and portions of 
Santa Ana, Anaheim, Westminster, Cypress, Stanton and Fountain Valley.JON 
NALICK 
</P>
