<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; COLLEGE CHOOSES 2 AS TEACHERS OF YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Irvine Valley College has selected two professors as Teachers of the Year. 
</P>
<P>
 The winners are Jeanne Egasse, a Spanish professor, and Vince Caiozzo, a human 
physiology professor. 
</P>
<P>
 Egasse, 42, lives in Santa Ana and has worked for the college since 1980. She 
also helped write a textbook for students of Spanish. Egasse holds a master's 
degree from UC Irvine in linguistics. 
</P>
<P>
 Caiozzo, 42, lives in Mission Viejo and has taught at the college for five 
years. He is also an instructor at UC Irvine's orthopedics department. He holds 
a doctorate in biology from UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
 Both teachers were selected by students. To nominate an instructor, students 
had to write a one-page essay describing why the teacher deserved the award. 
Egasse and Caiozzo were honored at the college's May 21 commencement.SHELBY 
GRAD 
