ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; PLANNING MEETING TO FOCUS ON TREES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents interested in helping shape the city's plan to improve the economic 
environment of the downtown area may attend a meeting of the Fullerton Downtown 
Planning Committee on July 11. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee, which was created by the City Council to study existing design 
guidelines for downtown businesses, will discuss a master plan for street trees 
at this session. 
</P>
<P>
 Committee members expect the discussion to include issues such as problems 
with sidewalks being lifted by tree roots and the obscuring of signs and lights 
by spreading branches. 
</P>
