<TEXT>
<P>
 A plan to build a volleyball court and install new playground equipment at 
Edison Park has received approval from the city's Parks Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 But opponents will have a final chance to halt the project when the City 
Council takes up the matter in the next few weeks. 
</P>
<P>
 College Park West residents have spent more than a year planning the park's 
first improvement project in more than 20 years. 
</P>
<P>
 The proposal has raised the ire of residents whose homes back onto the park. 
</P>
<P>
 They fear the volleyball court will increase noise and bring rowdy youths into 
the neighborhood. 
</P>
