EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SUN VALLEY; 19-YEAR-OLD FOUND SHOT TO DEATH IN CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIMOTHY WILLIAMS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 19-year-old Oakland man was fatally shot as he sat in his car outside a Sun 
Valley apartment building, Los Angeles police said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Patrol officers who were responding Sunday to a report of gunshots found 
Everado Loza slumped over in his car, which was parked at an apartment complex 
in the 7000 block of Bakman Avenue, said LAPD Detective Mike Coffey.Loza was 
pronounced dead at the scene by paramedics about 9:30 p.m. He had been shot 
several times in the upper torso, Coffey said. 
</P>
<P>
 Loza, who had recently moved to Oakland, was visiting relatives in Sun Valley, 
police said. 
