<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOUBLY DECISIVE DESIGNATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Once more, for those who may have missed it. . . . Just what does "D-day" 
mean? 
</P>
<P>
 Military historians remind that it is the consummate redundancy: The D in 
D-day stands for "Day." 
</P>
<P>
 Similarly, the H in H-hour (as in "D-day will begin at H-hour") stands for -- 
yes, "Hour." 
</P>
