 The deal calls for Martin Lawrence to sell $2 million principal amount of 
senior secured debt, together with warrants to purchase 250,000 common shares. 
In addition, Martin Lawrence will sell $1.5 million in convertible preferred 
stock to Herrick. The preferred stock is convertible into 3 million common 
shares, plus warrants to buy 4.58 million shares, which if exercised would 
provide Martin Lawrence up to $5.16 million in additional funds. 
