</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 3D Systems, the Valencia maker of machines that produce small-scale models of 
objects designed on computer screens, reported a profit of $828,561 in the 
first quarter that ended April 1, compared to a loss of $695,212 in the same 
period a year earlier. The turnaround was on a record revenue of $9.47 million, 
up 32% from $7.16 million a year earlier.  
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed the gain to increased sales due to growing acceptance 
of its devices, which manufacture plastic casts of designs so that engineers 
can get a three-dimensional representation of their ideas. 
</P>
