SPECIAL DEVICES REPORTS PROFIT OF $755,000 IN 2ND QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Special Devices Inc., a Newhall-based manufacturer of pyrotechnic devices for 
the automotive and aerospace industries, said its fiscal second-quarter profit 
more than tripled on an 81% surge in revenue. 
</P>
<P>
 For the three months ended May 1, Special Devices posted a profit of $755,000, 
up from $206,000 in the same quarter a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 Revenue increased to $15.3 million, from $8.47 million, because of greater 
shipments of devices that trigger air bags in automobiles. 
</P>
<P>
 The company, which also makes parts that ignite missiles, said automation 
helped boost operating margins and earnings. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six months ended May 1, the company showed a profit of $1.23 million, 
up from earnings of $294,000 a year earlier. Six-month revenue climbed 83%, to 
$27.6 million from $15.1 million. 
</P>
